E. COLI O104 - EUROPEAN UNION (31): UPDATE, DENMARK SECONDARY CASES
*******************************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] ECDC updates: new case definition
[2] Denmark ex Germany: secondary cases

*****
[1] ECDC updates: new case definition
Date: Fri 8 Jul 2011
Source: European Centre for Disease Control (ECDC) [edited]
http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/activities/sciadvice/Lists/ECDC%20Reviews/ECDC_DispForm.aspx?List=512ff74f%2D77d4%2D4ad8%2Db6d6%2Dbf0f23083f30&ID=1145&RootFolder=%2Fen%2Factivities%2Fsciadvice%2FLists%2FECDC%20Reviews


Update since 7 Jul 2011
-----------------------
As of today 8 Jul 2011, using the new case definition, the cumulative
number of non-HUS [hemolytic uremic syndrome] STEC [Shiga toxin
producing _Escherichia coli_] cases in the EU is 3024, including 16
deaths and 750 HUS cases, including 28 deaths. Suspected cases
(Germany: 154 HUS (7 deaths), France: 1 HUS, 8 non-HUS) are no longer
included.

In Germany, since 7 Jul 2011, 3 probable HUS cases have been
excluded, and 8 non-HUS STEC cases have been newly reported. 5 HUS
cases and 8 non-HUS STEC cases fell ill within the last 10 days (28
Jun-7 Jul 2011). The last known date of illness onset in a patient
with confirmed STEC O104 was 27 Jun 2011. The last reported date of
illness onset among all cases was 4 Jul 2011.

In Denmark, 1 HUS case and 1 non-HUS STEC case have been newly
reported. They have been attributed to person-to-person transmission,
from relatives who are known cases infected in Germany [see [2] below
- Mod.LL]

There is no update regarding the outbreak in France (Bordeaux
Region).

Update since 6 Jul 2011
-----------------------
The EU member states have updated the case definition for reporting
at the EU level the number of cases of STEC and HUS. At this stage of
the epidemic, where sporadic cases are still reported as well as new
limited clusters, only probable and confirmed epidemic cases are
reported. As a consequence, suspected cases, not meeting the case
definition have been removed from the totals. These are 152 HUS
including 7 deaths in Germany, 1 HUS, and 8 non-HUS STEC cases in
France.

As of today 7 Jul 2011, using the new case-definition, the cumulative
number of non-HUS STEC cases in the EU is 3016, including 16 deaths
and 752 HUS cases, including 28 deaths. In Germany, since 6 Jul 2011,
42 non-HUS STEC cases, 8 HUS cases including 2 deaths have been newly
reported. 5 HUS cases and 9 non-HUS STEC cases fell ill within the
last 10 days (27 Jun-6 Jul 2011). The last known date of illness onset
in a patient with confirmed STEC O104 was 27 Jun 2011. The last
reported date of illness onset among all cases was 4 Jul 2011.

There is no update regarding the outbreak in France (Bordeaux
Region).

